Why This Works for Potential Clients

Focused Experience: The content is distraction-free, guiding users toward taking the survey.
Trust and Credibility: Testimonials and trust signals (e.g., “Trusted by 100+ Organizations”) reassure clients of your expertise.
Engagement: The floated image and sample question make the page visually and interactively appealing.
Action-Oriented: The prominent CTA and clear benefits encourage immediate action.
Quarto-Friendly: The structure leverages Quarto’s markdown and CSS capabilities for easy implementation and customization.




Next Steps

Implement the Content: Update your index.qmd and styles.css with the provided code. Ensure images are in the images/ folder.
Test the Page: Use quarto preview to check the layout, especially the floated image and mobile responsiveness.
Add Analytics: Integrate Google Analytics to track engagement and refine based on data.
Gather Feedback: After launching, consider adding a short feedback form to collect user input on the landing page itself to optimize further.

If you need help with specific Quarto configurations or want me to analyze your current page further for tailored improvements, let me know! For more on survey landing page best practices, you can explore resources like Bitly’s guide or Opinion Stage.




